# Pre-deploy / post-deploy / live production checklist

**Canonical delivery standard:** **`.cursor/rules/delivery-reality.mdc`** — a change is only **COMPLETE** when **live production** matches intent; merge and CI are not enough.

## Pre-deploy / pre-infra-change

Before doing any **deployment**, **DNS/traffic split**, **tenant onboarding**, or **new “site/marketing” surface** work, do a quick “don’t redo / don’t contradict ourselves” pass:

- Read `docs/CORPFLOW_SHARED_TODO.md` (current priorities + what’s already done).
- Read `docs/EXECUTION_BRAIN_VS_HANDS.md` (brain vs hands boundaries; where 24/7 execution lives).
- For automation work, read `docs/automation-framework.md` and `docs/n8n/automation-forward-recipe.md`. Re-verify **ingest** (`CORPFLOW_AUTOMATION_INGEST_SECRET`), **forward** (`CORPFLOW_AUTOMATION_FORWARD_URL` / `*_SECRET`), **approval** secret if used, and **HMAC/header validation** on any new webhook — no silent widening of trust. See `docs/operations/SECURITY_REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md` § webhooks.
- For CMP behavior, skim `lib/cmp/README.md` (current API + tenancy rules).
- For **hostname, apex, tenant login, or `/api/tenant/site`**, read **`docs/operations/TENANT_CLIENT_LOGIN.md`** (tenancy model + checklist). Use **`artifacts/`** only as supplementary narrative, not as the sole source of truth.
- If the request references prior decisions about Luxe URLs, the **official** production site is **`https://lux.corpflowai.com/`**; **`luxe.corpflowai.com`** may exist only as an **optional alias** (same Vercel project + `tenant_hostnames`). Search docs and code and follow the current mapping.

## DNS / traffic split reminder

If apex vs `core.*` (or any hostnames) are moved onto different deployments/edge routing:

- Update GitHub secret `CORPFLOW_FACTORY_HEALTH_URL` (or add a second health workflow/job) so CI monitors the hostname clients actually use.
- Re-check tenant host mappings (`tenant_hostnames`) and any host-based tenancy derivation.

## Post-deploy: production identification (required)

Before calling any change **COMPLETE**, record:

- **Commit deployed** — full Git SHA on `main` that Vercel Production built (match GitHub merge commit to deployment).
- **Production deployment ID** — Vercel deployment id (e.g. `dpl_…`) for that Production build, **Ready**.
- **Live URLs tested** — list the exact production URLs you hit (not only Preview `*.vercel.app` unless the change is Preview-only by design).

If the fix is not on the **Production** deployment’s commit, **verdict cannot be COMPLETE** (see **delivery-reality.mdc**).

## Live production surface checks (closure / incident discipline)

**Repo + CI green does not prove customer-facing production is healthy.** A CMP ticket or change is not operationally complete until all of the following hold:

1. **CI** — required GitHub checks pass (including `vercel-env` and Agent CI / `test` workflow where applicable).
2. **Merge** — intended code is on `main` (or agreed release branch).
3. **Deployment** — Vercel Production deployment for that commit is **Ready** (not Error / canceled); note **deployment ID** + **commit**.
4. **Live surfaces** — verify **HTTP**, correct content type where relevant, and **absence of platform 5xx** on the **real hosts and paths clients use**.
5. **Observed behavior** — for the change, compare **expected vs actual** on production (not only “health JSON says ok”).

### Minimum live GET checks (production)

Use as a **floor**; **add** any host/path your change touches (tenant marketing, login, new routes).

| URL | Expected |
|-----|----------|
| `https://lux.corpflowai.com/` | **200** — Lux landing HTML (not `500`, not Vercel `MIDDLEWARE_INVOCATION_FAILED`) |
| `https://lux.corpflowai.com/change` | **200** — Change Console static route |
| `https://core.corpflowai.com/api/factory/health` | **200** — JSON `ok: true` |

**Health alone is not enough** for customer-visible changes: if **`/api/factory/health`** is **200** but **`lux.corpflowai.com/`** (or another required client URL) fails, the delivery verdict is **FAILED**, not COMPLETE.

If **`/`** fails but **`/change`** works, treat as **routing/middleware/platform** failure at the edge, not “app logic only.” **Postgres row status `Closed` is not sufficient** to claim operational completion when live URLs fail.

### Verdict (closure)

- **COMPLETE** — deployment ID + commit recorded; all required **live** checks pass; client-facing flow usable.
- **PARTIAL** — merged and/or deployed but audit incomplete, or verification intentionally pending (honest scope); **not** for “client URL broken but API ok.”
- **FAILED** — wrong commit on Production, deploy Error, or any required **client-facing** production URL/flow broken.

Use the **Delivery Reality Audit** block in **delivery-reality.mdc** for written closure.

### How to verify quickly

- Browser or `curl` / `Invoke-WebRequest` from an operator machine (sanity: status code + first bytes of HTML/JSON).
- Vercel → **Deployments** → Production → confirm **Ready** and **commit**; **Functions** / build output if 5xx persists.
- GitHub → **Deployments** or `gh api repos/.../deployments` to correlate **Production** with **SHA**.

